OL,5,Ctheorist
OL,7,F"They have both suffered life-changing
OL,8,Finjuries from which they will never
OL,9,Frecover," the barrister said.
OL,11,FThe court heard that Mr Hibbert
OL,12,Freceived 22 wounds from shrapnel, and
OL,13,FMiss Hibbert suffered a "catastrophic
OL,14,Fbrain injury" after a bolt from the
OL,15,Fbomb struck her in the head - leading
OL,16,Fto her being presumed dead at the
OL,17,Fscene.
OL,19,FThe teenager spent nine months in
OL,20,Fhospital and will require care for the
OL,21,Frest of her life.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@IO]uD@YOUvD@MO]
