OL,5,Ctheorist
OL,7,F"He doggedly adheres to the assertion
OL,8,Fthat this attack did not happen and
OL,9,Fthat we are all being fooled," Mr
OL,10,FPrice later said.
OL,12,FThe barrister said Mr Hall has claimed
OL,13,FMr Hibbert is lying, and that Miss
OL,14,FHibbert was disabled before the
OL,15,Fbombing.
OL,17,FHe continued: "Mr Hall says her
OL,18,Fparents are invoking their daughter's
OL,19,Fcatastrophic disability as part of a
OL,20,Fhuge fraud on the general public."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@^O]yD@OOU|D@bO]
