OL,3,CArena survivor hopes to protect
OL,4,Cdaughter from 'stalker man' conspiracy
OL,5,Ctheorist
OL,7,FMr Hibbert told the court Eve's
OL,8,Finjuries means she now has the
OL,9,Fcapacity of an eight or nine-year-old,
OL,10,Fand he has had to talk to her about
OL,11,Fthe case "in simple terms" to stop her
OL,12,Ffrom worrying about "the stalker man".
OL,14,FHe said he was taking the action to
OL,15,Fprotect her, and because she was
OL,16,Fscared.
OL,18,FPaul Oakley, for Mr Hall, said his
OL,19,Fclient is "entirely entitled" to have
OL,20,Fhis views, which were formed after he
OL,21,F"scoured the public domain".
OL,26,@{D@KOU{D@]O]}D@AOU}D@[O]
