OL,5,Ctheorist
OL,7,FHe told the court: "My client is
OL,8,Fperfectly entitled to hold his views
OL,9,Fand he is willing to amend them if he
OL,10,Fis made aware of evidence to the
OL,11,Fcontrary."
OL,13,FIn written submissions, Mr Oakley said
OL,14,FMr Hall and his beliefs have the right
OL,15,Fto freedom of expression.
OL,17,FHe said: "However unpleasant Mr Hall's
OL,18,Fpublished views are considered to be,
OL,19,Fthey are protected."
